WEBVTT

00:08.380 --> 00:09.860
- This is the club where I work.
- This is a New York address.

00:10.060 --> 00:12.200
Come by if you're ever in town.
I could show you around.

00:12.400 --> 00:14.740
<i>Previously on</i>
Daisy Jones and The Six...

00:14.940 --> 00:16.000
That's my voice.

00:16.200 --> 00:17.870
I just need to get out of here.

00:18.070 --> 00:18.960
- To where?
- To New York.

00:19.160 --> 00:21.390
I told you what that
woman said at the party.

00:22.690 --> 00:24.630
- "That woman."
- [chuckles softly]

00:24.830 --> 00:27.130
<i>[Daisy] And just like that,</i>
<i>she was gone.</i>

00:27.330 --> 00:29.590
<i>[Billy] We have</i>
<i>a new member of the band.</i>

00:29.790 --> 00:32.350
- Let's hear it for Daisy Jones.
- [band cheering]

00:32.540 --> 00:34.510
Why'd you want to join
the band in the first place?

00:34.710 --> 00:36.600
- You.
- What about me?

00:36.800 --> 00:38.450
<i>[Daisy] I feel like</i>
<i>I know you.</i>

00:41.080 --> 00:43.270
- It's not what you think, man.
- Okay.

00:43.470 --> 00:45.980
<i>Every song is like a coded</i>
<i>message from Billy to Daisy,</i>

00:46.180 --> 00:48.570
- Daisy to Billy.
- You make everything better.

00:48.770 --> 00:51.200
<i>[Daisy] Tell me that there's</i>
<i>nothing going on between us.</i>

00:51.400 --> 00:52.670
Tell me if I'm fucking crazy.

00:54.260 --> 00:55.450
<i>[Jonah] I could've sworn</i>
<i>you two were together.</i>

00:55.650 --> 00:57.120
How do you know we're not?

00:57.320 --> 00:58.330
Not according to Billy.

00:58.530 --> 00:59.600
You're a fucking liar.

01:01.020 --> 01:04.630
- Please, don't put
my daughter in your story.
- Give me something better then.

01:04.830 --> 01:06.380
<i>He doesn't actually have</i>
<i>feelings for you.</i>

01:06.580 --> 01:08.550
<i>He said it's</i>
<i>all about the music.</i>

01:08.750 --> 01:09.720
I'm looking for the woman
who lives here.

01:09.920 --> 01:11.090
<i>[woman] And how long were</i>
<i>you planning</i>

01:11.290 --> 01:12.340
<i>to stay in Greece, Miss Jones?</i>

01:12.540 --> 01:13.590
<i>[Daisy] You know,</i>

01:13.790 --> 01:15.490
<i>I never really think</i>
<i>that far ahead.</i>

01:18.120 --> 01:19.830
[♪ Patti Smith:
"Dancing Barefoot"]

01:21.740 --> 01:23.980
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:24.180 --> 01:26.070
♪ <i>Is benediction</i> ♪

01:26.270 --> 01:28.230
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:28.430 --> 01:30.280
♪ <i>Is addicted to thee</i> ♪

01:30.480 --> 01:32.450
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:32.650 --> 01:34.530
♪ <i>Is the root connection</i> ♪

01:34.730 --> 01:36.660
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:36.860 --> 01:38.750
♪ <i>Is connecting with he</i> ♪

01:38.940 --> 01:40.910
♪ <i>Here I go</i> ♪

01:41.110 --> 01:42.870
♪ <i>And I don't know why</i> ♪

01:43.070 --> 01:47.590
♪ <i>I fell so ceaselessly</i> ♪

01:47.790 --> 01:50.590
♪ <i>Could it be he's taking</i> ♪

01:50.790 --> 01:52.230
♪ <i>Over me</i> ♪

01:55.860 --> 02:00.140
♪ <i>I'm dancing barefoot</i> ♪

02:00.340 --> 02:04.150
♪ <i>Heading for a spin</i> ♪

02:04.340 --> 02:05.650
♪ <i>Some strange music</i> ♪

02:05.850 --> 02:08.690
♪ <i>Draws me in</i> ♪

02:08.890 --> 02:10.190
♪ <i>Makes me come on</i> ♪

02:10.390 --> 02:12.920
♪ <i>Like some heroine</i> ♪♪

02:22.300 --> 02:24.310
[♪ Jean Knight: "Carry On"]

02:30.230 --> 02:32.050
- ♪ <i>Whoo!</i> ♪
- Come here, baby.

02:32.250 --> 02:36.140
♪ <i>You got rhythm</i>
<i>in your soul</i> ♪

02:36.340 --> 02:40.100
♪ <i>You got the groove</i>
<i>under good control...</i>

02:40.300 --> 02:42.640
[knocking]

02:42.840 --> 02:45.270
Sorry. Full up.

02:45.470 --> 02:47.520
Oh, um, um...
I'm looking for Bernie.

02:47.720 --> 02:49.710
I'm... I'm kind of a friend.

02:59.430 --> 03:01.430
- [lively chatter]
- [music playing]

03:22.990 --> 03:24.850
I can't believe you came.

03:25.050 --> 03:27.450
Well, you said I had
to see it, so...

03:30.330 --> 03:32.900
You weren't kidding, either.

03:33.100 --> 03:34.340
Admit it.

03:39.300 --> 03:41.630
You remember that surprise
I promised you?

03:49.430 --> 03:51.630
♪ <i>You know your love</i>
<i>ain't enough...</i>

03:51.830 --> 03:53.770
[crowd cheering]

03:56.360 --> 03:58.130
I don't understand.

03:58.330 --> 04:00.220
I took the vocals you sent me.

04:00.420 --> 04:02.560
I added some tracks
for the crowd and...

04:02.750 --> 04:04.740
they can't get enough of it.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.980
Check it out.

04:08.180 --> 04:10.290
You've got fans.

04:14.170 --> 04:16.960
♪ <i>It's your love, you know</i> ♪

04:18.960 --> 04:23.090
♪ <i>'Cause you know</i> ♪

04:25.300 --> 04:28.260
♪ <i>Your love ain't enough</i> ♪♪

04:29.560 --> 04:31.790
I don't usually...

04:31.990 --> 04:33.670
wake up with people.

04:33.870 --> 04:35.210
Mm. [chuckles]

04:35.410 --> 04:37.210
- 'Cause you're cold, huh?
- [laughs]

04:37.410 --> 04:39.720
You just, uh...
kick 'em right out of bed.

04:39.920 --> 04:41.440
No, I just, um...

04:44.740 --> 04:46.370
Yes.

04:54.290 --> 04:56.440
♪ <i>Your love ain't enough...</i>

04:56.640 --> 04:59.130
Look at that,
they know all the lyrics.

05:00.460 --> 05:02.460
Hey, you know what would
really make them go crazy?

05:09.810 --> 05:11.750
[microphone feedback screeches]

05:11.950 --> 05:14.000
My beautiful brothers...

05:14.200 --> 05:16.130
my lovely sisters...

05:16.330 --> 05:17.760
[cheering]

05:17.950 --> 05:20.090
...here she is, in the flesh.

05:20.290 --> 05:22.720
The Lady Simone!

05:22.920 --> 05:24.860
[crowd cheering]

05:31.580 --> 05:33.870
♪ ♪

05:39.630 --> 05:42.740
♪ <i>When I was down,</i>
<i>I couldn't see</i> ♪

05:42.940 --> 05:45.990
♪ <i>The world was a dark place,</i>
<i>but you showed me</i> ♪

05:46.190 --> 05:49.750
♪ <i>Your light,</i>
<i>how to live my life</i> ♪

05:49.950 --> 05:54.210
♪ <i>And you swept me</i>
<i>off my feet</i> ♪

05:54.410 --> 05:57.670
♪ <i>Now I gotta sing</i>
<i>though I don't want to</i> ♪

05:57.870 --> 06:01.840
♪ <i>There's nothing else</i>
<i>for me to say but</i> ♪

06:02.040 --> 06:04.340
♪ <i>Don't tell me</i>
<i>you're in love</i> ♪

06:04.540 --> 06:07.300
♪ <i>'Cause you know that ain't</i> ♪

06:07.500 --> 06:11.270
♪ <i>Know that ain't enough...</i>

06:11.470 --> 06:13.890
<i>I could've sang</i>
<i>that song all night.</i>

06:14.090 --> 06:16.560
<i>The crazy thing is,</i>
<i>they would've let me.</i>

06:16.760 --> 06:18.400
Again?

06:18.600 --> 06:20.230
How many times
are we gonna do this?

06:20.430 --> 06:22.570
As many as we can.

06:22.770 --> 06:25.110
You've only got the one song.

06:25.310 --> 06:27.260
Yeah.

06:28.340 --> 06:30.080
Well, maybe we should
work on that.

06:30.280 --> 06:32.960
Mm, maybe we should.

06:33.160 --> 06:34.580
Stop.

06:34.780 --> 06:37.170
People are watching.

06:37.370 --> 06:39.130
Sorry.

06:39.330 --> 06:41.340
One more time.

06:41.540 --> 06:43.420
♪ <i>'Cause you know that you</i> ♪

06:43.620 --> 06:46.680
♪ <i>Know that you and I</i> ♪♪

06:46.880 --> 06:49.850
I'd just rather be
low key about it.

06:50.050 --> 06:52.060
That's all.

06:52.260 --> 06:54.330
I mean,
what are you so scared of?

06:57.910 --> 07:00.070
Isn't it obvious?

07:00.270 --> 07:02.210
Look.

07:04.130 --> 07:05.610
There's always
gonna be somewhere

07:05.810 --> 07:07.460
where we have to be careful.

07:08.920 --> 07:10.790
But in the club,

07:10.980 --> 07:13.370
with our people, baby...

07:13.570 --> 07:16.220
come on, if we can't dance
there, where can we?

07:19.020 --> 07:20.880
I just don't want
to keep hiding something

07:21.080 --> 07:23.360
that feels this good.

07:25.440 --> 07:26.760
Mm-hmm.

07:26.960 --> 07:28.550
<i>She was right.</i>

07:28.750 --> 07:30.680
<i>I was hiding.</i>

07:30.880 --> 07:33.530
<i>And I wasn't yet ready</i>
<i>to stop.</i>

07:35.080 --> 07:38.060
<i>So I put everything I was</i>
<i>feeling into the music.</i>

07:38.260 --> 07:40.480
♪ <i>People say</i> ♪

07:40.680 --> 07:42.880
♪ <i>I'm free</i> ♪

07:45.710 --> 07:49.410
♪ <i>But you don't know me...</i>

07:49.610 --> 07:52.120
<i>And once I did...</i>

07:52.320 --> 07:55.120
that song...

07:55.320 --> 07:57.160
just...

07:57.360 --> 07:58.870
worked.

07:59.070 --> 08:01.020
[crowd cheering]

08:06.110 --> 08:09.400
♪ <i>People say I'm free</i> ♪

08:12.740 --> 08:16.270
♪ <i>But they don't know me...</i>

08:16.470 --> 08:19.150
<i>I mean,</i>
<i>that's how it was back then.</i>

08:19.340 --> 08:21.540
<i>We had to do</i>
<i>everything ourselves.</i>

08:23.540 --> 08:25.110
<i>We put it out on a tiny label</i>

08:25.310 --> 08:28.030
<i>and hand-delivered copies</i>
<i>to every</i>

08:28.230 --> 08:30.240
<i>- DJ we knew.</i>
- [bicycle bell dings]

08:30.440 --> 08:32.670
<i>God, it was fun!</i>

08:33.970 --> 08:36.950
<i>Suddenly Bernie and I were</i>
<i>doing four shows a night.</i>

08:37.150 --> 08:38.960
♪ <i>I'm free...</i>

08:39.160 --> 08:42.210
<i>In the Midtown clubs where</i>
<i>the mainstreamers danced.</i>

08:42.410 --> 08:45.810
♪ <i>You will find out</i>
<i>you were wrong...</i>

08:46.980 --> 08:49.930
<i>The roller discos</i>
<i>in Central Jersey.</i>

08:50.130 --> 08:52.720
♪ <i>This is our</i>
<i>last night together...</i>

08:52.920 --> 08:55.680
<i>All we had to do was</i>
<i>play two songs,</i>

08:55.880 --> 08:57.470
<i>and people lost their minds.</i>

08:57.670 --> 09:00.450
♪ <i>No man</i> ♪

09:02.330 --> 09:06.400
♪ <i>To lead me</i>
<i>to the promised land...</i>

09:06.600 --> 09:09.570
<i>But we always ended our nights</i>
<i>back at "Better Days."</i>

09:09.770 --> 09:12.660
♪ <i>Get around,</i>
<i>say what you want...</i>

09:12.860 --> 09:15.340
<i>They knew what the song</i>
<i>was really about.</i>

09:16.340 --> 09:20.100
♪ <i>Callin' me</i>
<i>and my friends deviants</i> ♪

09:23.890 --> 09:27.850
♪ <i>What my condition is</i> ♪

09:30.400 --> 09:32.890
♪ <i>It ain't the same as</i> ♪

09:33.080 --> 09:36.610
♪ <i>What my mission is,</i>
<i>what my mission is</i> ♪

09:38.280 --> 09:41.890
♪ <i>I am a diamond</i>
<i>under pressure...</i>

09:42.090 --> 09:43.600
<i>I may not have been</i>

09:43.800 --> 09:45.690
<i>comfortable enough yet</i>
<i>to dance with her...</i>

09:45.890 --> 09:49.570
♪ <i>I'm a diamond</i>
<i>under pressure</i> ♪

09:49.770 --> 09:51.820
<i>But making music together,</i>

09:52.020 --> 09:54.700
<i>making everyone else dance,</i>

09:54.900 --> 09:57.700
<i>it was the next best thing.</i>

09:57.900 --> 10:00.390
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

10:02.850 --> 10:04.920
Hello.

10:05.120 --> 10:07.290
Yeah, one sec.

10:07.490 --> 10:10.060
[whispers] It's for you.

10:13.190 --> 10:15.340
- Hello?
<i>- [Teddy] Hey, Simone.</i>

10:15.540 --> 10:17.680
Oh, hey, Teddy.

10:17.880 --> 10:19.520
<i>- So who's that?</i>
- Uh...

10:19.710 --> 10:21.350
that's just my roommate.

10:21.550 --> 10:23.520
How's my girl doing?

10:23.720 --> 10:25.350
You still burning down
those clubs?

10:25.550 --> 10:27.940
<i>Three a night. Sometimes four.</i>

10:28.140 --> 10:30.780
[chuckles]
I'm so proud of you.

10:30.980 --> 10:32.440
How's things in La-La Land?

10:32.640 --> 10:35.280
Well, actually, uh, that's,
uh, why I'm calling you.

10:35.480 --> 10:37.450
Have you spoken
to Daisy recently?

10:37.650 --> 10:39.160
No, it's been a few weeks.

10:39.360 --> 10:41.120
Why, is everything okay?

10:41.320 --> 10:44.120
<i>Probably. We-we had</i>
<i>a record release party.</i>

10:44.320 --> 10:46.630
<i>- And she didn't bother to show.</i>
- Sounds like Daisy to me.

10:46.830 --> 10:48.880
I was just wondering
if you knew anything.

10:49.080 --> 10:51.170
<i>No, I don't. But, uh,</i>

10:51.370 --> 10:53.920
I'm sure it's nothing.
She wouldn't miss the tour.

10:54.120 --> 10:56.140
<i>Well, you'll let me know</i>
<i>if you hear anything, right?</i>

10:56.330 --> 10:58.850
- Yeah, of course.
<i>- All right, baby.</i>

10:59.050 --> 11:01.350
Bye.

11:01.550 --> 11:03.490
- [line clicks]
- [dial tone drones]

11:07.290 --> 11:08.940
[chuckles]

11:09.140 --> 11:11.030
"Just my roommate."

11:11.220 --> 11:13.610
- Shut up, shut up!
- It's nothing... oh!

11:13.810 --> 11:15.450
You know, Daisy and I
had been keeping in touch,

11:15.650 --> 11:17.450
but it wasn't like
we spoke every day and...

11:17.650 --> 11:19.830
You know, I-I really
didn't think anything of it.

11:20.020 --> 11:21.490
<i>I had my own thing going on.</i>

11:21.690 --> 11:23.040
[indistinct chatter]

11:23.240 --> 11:25.040
[cameras clicking]

11:25.240 --> 11:27.500
[fan] Simone! Simone! Simone!

11:27.700 --> 11:30.040
So who's gonna be at the Sahara?

11:30.240 --> 11:33.050
Leslie, uh, Lena, Alice...

11:33.250 --> 11:35.840
Alice? Alice never shows up.

11:36.040 --> 11:37.430
Thank you.

11:37.630 --> 11:39.140
And, um...

11:39.340 --> 11:40.890
What?
Why are you making that face?

11:41.090 --> 11:42.350
I don't know
if I should tell you or not.

11:42.550 --> 11:44.270
- I don't know
if I should tell you.
- Oh!

11:44.470 --> 11:46.640
- Come on, tell me.
- [laughs]

11:46.840 --> 11:48.410
Bernie!

11:49.450 --> 11:50.940
Thank you.

11:51.140 --> 11:52.940
Tell me.

11:53.140 --> 11:54.880
Come on, tell me.

11:59.710 --> 12:02.160
Some execs from Salsoul are
gonna meet us at the club.

12:02.360 --> 12:04.120
They want to press the record.

12:04.320 --> 12:07.580
Oh, my God! That's amazing!
That's amazing!

12:07.780 --> 12:09.170
- I know, right?
- [knocking]

12:09.370 --> 12:11.670
- Miss Jackson?
- Yes?

12:11.870 --> 12:14.600
- Telegram for you.
- Oh, thank you, Chloe.

12:15.650 --> 12:17.360
What?

12:22.450 --> 12:23.560
What?

12:23.760 --> 12:25.910
What, what is it?

12:29.290 --> 12:31.610
It's called Hydra, Hee-dra.

12:31.800 --> 12:34.270
It's some island
in Greece apparently.

12:34.470 --> 12:36.240
And you're just gonna fly there.

12:36.430 --> 12:38.030
Tonight. Just like that?

12:38.230 --> 12:39.910
I mean,

12:40.100 --> 12:42.240
what about the shows we booked?

12:42.440 --> 12:44.330
She doesn't have anyone else.

12:44.530 --> 12:46.760
She could be in jail,
she could be...

13:03.360 --> 13:06.200
Well, you sure as hell ain't
going to Greece by yourself.

13:07.490 --> 13:09.490
[♪ Les Terribles: "Chouchou"]

13:15.790 --> 13:17.790
♪ ♪

13:22.550 --> 13:24.550
<i>[singing in French]</i>

13:41.360 --> 13:44.090
[indistinct chatter]

13:44.290 --> 13:45.390
Hi, do you know if there...

13:45.590 --> 13:47.760
There may be a taxi
that can take us there?

13:47.960 --> 13:49.390
Taxi? Taxi?

13:49.590 --> 13:51.100
[speaks Greek]

13:51.300 --> 13:53.190
Taxi!

13:53.390 --> 13:55.020
[speaks Greek]

13:55.220 --> 13:57.170
♪ ♪

13:58.170 --> 14:00.170
It's got to be one of these.

14:02.460 --> 14:04.620
- Oh, maybe it's that door.
- You think so?

14:04.810 --> 14:07.380
- We passed...
- Simone! Simone! [laughs]

14:08.800 --> 14:13.000
[laughing] Ah! Simone!
Oh, my God!

14:13.200 --> 14:14.330
You came!

14:14.530 --> 14:15.670
- Yeah.
- I can't believe you came.

14:15.870 --> 14:17.290
- Hi, Bernie.
- Hey. Yeah.

14:17.490 --> 14:18.960
Daisy. Hi.

14:19.160 --> 14:21.340
- Are you okay?
- Of course I'm okay.
Why wouldn't I be?

14:21.540 --> 14:23.380
Well, you disappeared.

14:23.580 --> 14:25.390
And no one heard
from you for weeks and...

14:25.590 --> 14:27.180
you wrote me this.

14:27.380 --> 14:28.560
I brought bail money.

14:28.760 --> 14:30.060
[laughs]

14:30.260 --> 14:32.520
I'm sorry, I didn't mean...

14:32.720 --> 14:34.770
I can see how this, this, uh...

14:34.970 --> 14:36.310
feels alarming, but I...

14:36.510 --> 14:39.250
- So you're not in trouble?
- I'm not in trouble.

14:41.170 --> 14:42.920
I'm getting married.

14:44.880 --> 14:46.370
Nicky?

14:46.560 --> 14:48.510
[sighs]
Nicky?

14:50.550 --> 14:52.580
- They're here!
- [door opens]

14:52.780 --> 14:54.390
Nicky?

14:56.810 --> 14:59.590
Simone, Bernie,
this is my fiancé...

14:59.790 --> 15:01.000
[both laugh]

15:01.200 --> 15:02.420
...Nicky Fitzpatrick.

15:02.620 --> 15:04.090
It's a pleasure.

15:04.290 --> 15:05.590
I've heard so much about you.

15:05.790 --> 15:07.590
Please, please, come in.

15:07.790 --> 15:10.390
Make yourselves comfortable.
I'll-I'll get you a drink.

15:10.590 --> 15:13.640
♪ ♪

15:13.840 --> 15:16.060
And there I was just sitting
in my hotel room, spinning out,

15:16.260 --> 15:19.110
and I figured I might as well

15:19.310 --> 15:21.080
go to Greece.

15:26.000 --> 15:27.910
[sighs]

15:28.110 --> 15:30.080
I know that you think
that this is crazy,

15:30.270 --> 15:32.490
but he's just not like
anybody I've ever met.

15:32.690 --> 15:35.710
He lives in the moment,
and he's free.

15:35.910 --> 15:37.750
And I told him
I couldn't marry him

15:37.950 --> 15:39.750
without my maid of honor here.

15:39.950 --> 15:42.750
So that's why I wrote.

15:42.950 --> 15:44.340
[Simone clears throat quietly]

15:44.540 --> 15:47.260
Well, uh, maybe next time,
use a telephone.

15:47.460 --> 15:49.090
[laughing]

15:49.290 --> 15:50.510
[laughs]

15:50.710 --> 15:53.350
Here. This is just to start.

15:53.550 --> 15:55.740
Thank you.

15:57.240 --> 16:00.120
So what do you think
of The Six, Nicky?

16:01.500 --> 16:04.710
The Six? Uh, the six of what?

16:07.880 --> 16:09.710
You never heard her music?

16:11.420 --> 16:12.910
I thought you were a poet.

16:13.110 --> 16:15.080
[laughs]
I'm afraid

16:15.280 --> 16:18.080
my musical tastes
are a little, uh, restrained.

16:18.280 --> 16:22.020
But I have heard her sing,
and her voice is... beautiful.

16:27.480 --> 16:29.050
This has to be, like,
the best thing I've ever eaten.

16:29.250 --> 16:30.470
[laughter]

16:30.670 --> 16:32.760
So this is your home?

16:32.960 --> 16:35.470
Um, in a way, yes. Yeah.

16:35.670 --> 16:37.310
I spend as much time here
as I can.

16:37.510 --> 16:41.940
But I keep houses in, uh,
Rome and back in Ireland,

16:42.140 --> 16:45.000
where I have a few obligations.

16:46.580 --> 16:47.990
What is it that you do, Nicky?

16:48.190 --> 16:49.950
I am a student,

16:50.150 --> 16:51.490
working on a dissertation.

16:51.690 --> 16:54.530
But you own this house?

16:54.730 --> 16:56.260
Yes.

16:57.680 --> 17:02.420
[Bernie] And you have places
in Rome and Ireland?

17:02.620 --> 17:03.960
- You should just tell them.
- [Daisy and Nicky laugh]

17:04.160 --> 17:05.800
[Nicky] Um,

17:06.000 --> 17:08.720
my family are members of a...

17:08.920 --> 17:11.220
non-ruling, sovereign nobility
back in Ireland.

17:11.420 --> 17:13.260
Wa-Wait. Are you a prince?

17:13.460 --> 17:15.260
[quietly]
This is why I don't tell people.

17:15.460 --> 17:17.970
His family goes back
to the 13th century in Ireland,

17:18.170 --> 17:19.640
and they have a castle.

17:19.840 --> 17:21.520
[Nicky] Castle.
Yes, I have a castle.

17:21.720 --> 17:23.770
- Very old and moldy castle.
- [Daisy laughs]

17:23.970 --> 17:25.860
The whole thing is,
uh, very meaningless

17:26.060 --> 17:27.820
outside a small aristocracy.

17:28.020 --> 17:30.990
Hmm. Hey, to your wedding.

17:31.190 --> 17:32.280
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

17:32.480 --> 17:33.780
[Nicky] Cheers.

17:33.980 --> 17:36.910
Mmm.

17:37.110 --> 17:39.050
♪ ♪

18:05.160 --> 18:08.170
[Daisy strumming gentle melody
on bouzouki]

18:15.260 --> 18:16.660
What happened to your guitar?

18:16.860 --> 18:18.410
I had my stash
in the guitar case,

18:18.610 --> 18:20.930
and there were cops everywhere,
so I just left it.

18:21.970 --> 18:24.420
And then, Nicky bought me this.

18:24.620 --> 18:26.920
You got better
while you were recording.

18:27.120 --> 18:29.050
I know. [laughs]

18:29.250 --> 18:31.190
[Daisy continues playing]

18:33.230 --> 18:35.010
I can't picture it.

18:35.210 --> 18:36.890
His Highness in there

18:37.090 --> 18:39.060
sleeping in a cramped tour bus
with your bandmates

18:39.260 --> 18:41.480
for seven months,

18:41.670 --> 18:43.740
eight months.

18:45.750 --> 18:47.610
He won't have to.

18:47.810 --> 18:49.040
Why not?

18:52.340 --> 18:54.210
Because I'm not gonna go back.

18:56.420 --> 18:58.490
[Simone chuckles]

18:58.690 --> 19:00.640
Daisy.

19:07.270 --> 19:09.130
Did you even see this?

19:09.330 --> 19:11.050
I almost cried.

19:11.250 --> 19:14.590
The-the newsstand guy must've
thought I was losing my mind.

19:14.790 --> 19:16.590
Yeah, I did. I saw it.

19:16.790 --> 19:18.990
And I read it, too.

19:23.740 --> 19:26.350
Why would I ever go back
to that, Simone,

19:26.550 --> 19:28.860
when I have everything
that I want here?

19:29.060 --> 19:30.920
[scoffs softly]

19:31.960 --> 19:33.940
Come on. You can't be serious.

19:34.140 --> 19:36.090
I am.

19:39.670 --> 19:43.140
That's you on the cover
of <i>Rolling Stone.</i>

19:49.600 --> 19:51.560
No, it's not.

20:14.330 --> 20:17.090
♪ ♪

20:49.580 --> 20:51.200
[folds magazine]

20:59.630 --> 21:01.510
- [door closes]
- Hi.

21:09.600 --> 21:12.100
I can't wait to marry you.

21:25.280 --> 21:27.220
♪ ♪

21:27.420 --> 21:29.410
[indistinct chatter]

21:31.240 --> 21:33.250
[speaking Greek]

21:39.630 --> 21:42.300
- That's my favorite.
- That-that one?

21:44.880 --> 21:46.660
[laughing softly]

21:46.860 --> 21:48.080
[indistinct chatter]

21:48.280 --> 21:49.830
[Freddie] Ah!

21:50.030 --> 21:51.500
[speaking Greek]

21:51.700 --> 21:53.580
Hey, Nicky Nick. Late as always.

21:53.780 --> 21:55.540
Freddie, I'm on island time.

21:55.740 --> 21:59.130
[laughing]

21:59.330 --> 22:02.440
[man] Hey, <i>mon frère,</i>
come over here!

22:03.610 --> 22:05.470
[speaking Greek]

22:05.670 --> 22:07.610
♪ ♪

22:09.700 --> 22:11.560
You already know this monster.

22:11.760 --> 22:15.110
Avoid him at all costs.

22:15.300 --> 22:17.250
Whoo!

22:20.130 --> 22:21.990
- This is Giorgios.
- Hi.

22:22.190 --> 22:24.200
He makes beautiful portraits,
all in gold leaf.

22:24.400 --> 22:26.740
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

22:26.940 --> 22:29.080
And here is Petros,

22:29.280 --> 22:32.330
holding court as usual.

22:32.530 --> 22:35.180
This is Manala shit.
Finest quality.

22:36.640 --> 22:39.460
I wrote 28 stanzas
of an epic poem

22:39.660 --> 22:41.460
under its magnificent influence.

22:41.660 --> 22:42.880
[laughing]

22:43.080 --> 22:44.430
Well, Daisy's also a poet,

22:44.630 --> 22:46.180
so you two are going
to love each other.

22:46.380 --> 22:47.720
Well, we'll see about that.

22:47.920 --> 22:49.760
What do you write about, Daisy?

22:49.960 --> 22:51.770
I write about...

22:51.970 --> 22:53.810
whatever I want to.

22:54.010 --> 22:55.810
Mostly, she writes
about loneliness.

22:56.010 --> 22:57.690
- Ah.
- What do you write about?

22:57.890 --> 23:00.820
Everything. Love, madness.

23:01.020 --> 23:03.400
- Mostly love and madness.
- [Daisy laughs]

23:03.600 --> 23:05.780
[Mary] Petros won a big prize
for his poetry.

23:05.980 --> 23:07.780
[Petros] Oh, boy.

23:07.980 --> 23:09.780
- Four years ago?
- [Petros] Yes.

23:09.980 --> 23:11.370
Stopped publishing after that.

23:11.570 --> 23:13.500
Why'd you stop publishing?

23:13.700 --> 23:16.750
I didn't. I just say "no"
to the moneymen,

23:16.950 --> 23:18.790
but still, I write every day.

23:18.990 --> 23:20.880
How do people read it?

23:21.080 --> 23:24.510
Come to our house.
The door's always open.

23:24.710 --> 23:27.430
Um, sorry. I don't understand.

23:27.630 --> 23:29.970
Isn't the whole point
of making stuff

23:30.170 --> 23:34.310
for it to be seen, heard,
you know, shared?

23:34.510 --> 23:36.640
[Giorgios] No, no, the point is
in the making, my dear.

23:36.840 --> 23:38.860
That's where the joy is.

23:39.050 --> 23:41.440
Our job is to stay
in a state of grace.

23:41.640 --> 23:44.750
Everything else
is just, um, applause.

23:46.630 --> 23:48.360
He's right, you know.

23:48.560 --> 23:51.700
Never let other people tell you
whether your work has value

23:51.900 --> 23:54.120
because then, they own you.

23:54.320 --> 23:56.460
Now I write for myself,

23:56.660 --> 23:59.330
for my friends, for the waves.

23:59.530 --> 24:01.350
It's more pure.

24:11.400 --> 24:14.030
♪ ♪

24:16.910 --> 24:21.230
[speaking Greek]

24:21.430 --> 24:23.570
I've never seen Nicky so happy.

24:23.770 --> 24:25.820
Yeah. That's what I said.

24:26.020 --> 24:28.550
He seems like the kind of person
that's always happy.

24:30.550 --> 24:32.410
No?

24:32.610 --> 24:34.410
Um...

24:34.610 --> 24:37.790
Nicky's parents died
in a car crash a few years ago.

24:37.990 --> 24:40.750
And for a long time,
he was quite closed off.

24:40.950 --> 24:43.590
Even until recently.

24:43.790 --> 24:46.460
And you had the feeling like

24:46.660 --> 24:49.090
he was seeing his life
through a telescope,

24:49.290 --> 24:51.300
from far away.

24:51.500 --> 24:53.350
But, now, with you,

24:53.550 --> 24:56.450
I think that
he's finally living again.

24:59.160 --> 25:01.330
[quiet chatter]

25:06.710 --> 25:10.490
♪ <i>Say, in every case,</i>
<i>there must be rules</i> ♪

25:10.690 --> 25:14.370
♪ <i>We don't take them for</i>
<i>granted, we're not fools...</i>

25:14.570 --> 25:18.290
Oh, I never knew
the sky could look like this.

25:18.490 --> 25:20.500
You know, being a city kid
and all.

25:20.700 --> 25:22.580
[both laugh]

25:22.780 --> 25:24.770
Feels like
we're on another planet.

25:26.100 --> 25:27.800
- Well...
- Mm.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.220
...we kind of are.

25:30.420 --> 25:31.930
I mean, nobody knows us here.

25:32.130 --> 25:33.430
No.

25:33.630 --> 25:37.060
And we can do what we want.

25:37.260 --> 25:39.240
We don't have to worry.

25:41.450 --> 25:44.540
But the problem is,
we're gonna have to go home.

25:47.000 --> 25:49.380
You know we can have this
at home, right?

25:52.460 --> 25:54.670
Hey, can I tell you something?

25:57.390 --> 25:59.970
I'm in love with you.

26:04.930 --> 26:07.310
You don't have
to say anything back.

26:11.320 --> 26:13.730
I just need you to know.

26:19.450 --> 26:21.980
- They all loved you.
- Of course they did.

26:22.180 --> 26:24.520
- [laughs]
- Are you surprised
that they liked me?

26:24.720 --> 26:26.750
So surprised.

26:28.170 --> 26:30.070
No. It was great.

26:30.270 --> 26:32.340
I'm very happy.

26:36.260 --> 26:38.550
Why didn't you tell me
about your parents?

26:42.180 --> 26:44.120
I'm really sorry.

26:44.320 --> 26:46.330
Don't be sorry.

26:46.530 --> 26:48.590
I'm here, and I'm with you.

26:48.790 --> 26:50.730
That's all that matters.

26:51.730 --> 26:53.770
I don't know
if that's all that matters.

27:03.990 --> 27:05.980
I was sad for a long time
afterwards.

27:06.180 --> 27:09.400
But at some point,
my sadness became a choice.

27:09.600 --> 27:13.320
So what do you do if you have
a problem or something's wrong?

27:13.520 --> 27:15.360
You just look away?

27:15.560 --> 27:18.010
I look at the good things
in life.

27:20.130 --> 27:22.720
I look at you,
and the rest just disappears.

27:28.140 --> 27:30.710
It's like the Buddhists say.

27:30.910 --> 27:33.010
"Pain is inevitable.

27:33.210 --> 27:35.400
Suffering is optional."

27:40.570 --> 27:43.570
We had this artistic and...

27:45.700 --> 27:47.690
...emotional connection.

27:47.890 --> 27:52.290
I let him in,
and he messed with my head.

27:53.330 --> 27:56.070
I think I thought
that we were, you know,

27:56.270 --> 27:58.450
like, soulmates or...

27:58.650 --> 28:01.910
I thought
I found my soulmate once.

28:02.110 --> 28:03.950
- Francesca.
- [laughs softly]

28:04.150 --> 28:06.290
We were very alike.

28:06.490 --> 28:08.670
I think...

28:08.870 --> 28:12.060
it's easy to confuse a soulmate
with a mirror.

28:13.600 --> 28:15.150
Maybe.

28:20.070 --> 28:22.070
Maybe he was a mirror.

28:32.330 --> 28:35.670
This, um...
connection you had...

28:37.590 --> 28:39.920
...it's gone, right?

29:04.860 --> 29:06.390
<i>[Daisy] Well,</i>
<i>she came here with you.</i>

29:06.590 --> 29:08.390
That sounds serious to me.

29:08.590 --> 29:11.310
- Maybe.
- But?

29:11.510 --> 29:13.500
[Simone chuckles]

29:17.630 --> 29:21.010
I don't want to be playing
small clubs forever, Daisy.

29:22.380 --> 29:24.240
I want what you got.

29:24.440 --> 29:27.140
Why can't you have both?

29:28.180 --> 29:31.170
Can I ask you something?

29:31.370 --> 29:34.270
You sure you know
what you're doing?

29:36.310 --> 29:38.710
Last time we spoke, it sounded
like you were in the middle

29:38.910 --> 29:40.720
of getting your heart broken.

29:40.920 --> 29:43.180
Oh, that feels like
a lifetime ago now.

29:43.380 --> 29:44.570
But it wasn't.

29:46.570 --> 29:47.640
It was a month ago.

29:47.840 --> 29:50.080
And I'm here now, Simone.

29:52.080 --> 29:55.860
Billy made me miserable,
and Nicky makes me happy.

29:56.060 --> 29:59.440
And I just want to be...

29:59.640 --> 30:01.050
happy.

30:02.460 --> 30:05.700
For once, I want to be the one
that gets to be happy.

30:05.900 --> 30:08.010
I mean,
can't you understand that?

30:16.350 --> 30:18.380
Okay.

30:18.580 --> 30:20.720
[Petros] The rings, please.

30:20.910 --> 30:22.860
[strumming gentle melody]

30:43.800 --> 30:45.450
- Hi.
- [laughing] Hi.

30:45.650 --> 30:46.950
[Nicky laughs]

30:47.150 --> 30:48.870
Now let them make,
one to the other,

30:49.070 --> 30:52.050
those vows which
are between them and the gods.

30:54.140 --> 30:56.920
- [applause]
- Now let's let the sky hear

30:57.120 --> 31:01.510
and the waves listen
to their sound.

31:01.710 --> 31:03.670
<i>- Na zisete.</i>
- [bell ringing]

31:03.870 --> 31:05.470
[all] <i>Na zisete.</i>

31:05.670 --> 31:07.390
[bells ringing]

31:07.590 --> 31:09.390
[Nicky laughs]

31:09.590 --> 31:13.600
[whooping, cheering]

31:13.800 --> 31:18.020
You know, I've done a lot
of dumb things in my life.

31:18.220 --> 31:22.190
Really dumb. Things that
I'll regret until the day I die.

31:22.390 --> 31:24.820
[muted lively chatter]

31:25.020 --> 31:27.210
But I don't regret that day.

31:33.100 --> 31:35.890
♪ ♪

31:56.830 --> 31:58.830
Come on.

32:00.210 --> 32:02.670
- We're leaving already?
- No.

32:25.110 --> 32:26.610
Hey.

32:29.400 --> 32:31.300
I love you, too.

32:31.500 --> 32:34.110
[laughs]
No shit.

32:36.330 --> 32:38.910
But I'm glad
you finally figured it out.

32:57.010 --> 32:58.500
- [cork pops]
- [cheering]

32:58.700 --> 32:59.710
[bells ringing]

32:59.910 --> 33:03.350
- [rock music plays softly]
- [cheering]

33:13.900 --> 33:15.470
- Congratulations.
- Thank you very much.

33:15.670 --> 33:17.100
- [Simone laughs]
- Cheers.

33:17.300 --> 33:19.240
- Cheers.
- [laughs]

33:27.290 --> 33:28.570
You think it's crazy,
right? [laughs]

33:28.770 --> 33:29.860
No, no, no, I...

33:30.060 --> 33:32.740
I don't. Um...

33:32.940 --> 33:34.240
I think it's sudden.

33:34.440 --> 33:36.510
Yeah, yeah, true.

33:39.010 --> 33:41.080
Crazy would be
staying here forever,

33:41.280 --> 33:44.560
not going on tour with the band
she took to number one.

33:46.980 --> 33:49.270
Nobody tells Daisy what to do.

33:51.610 --> 33:53.470
Well, you're her husband now.

33:53.670 --> 33:55.470
You can talk some sense
into her.

33:55.670 --> 33:58.390
[Nicky laughs]

33:58.590 --> 34:00.620
I could try, yes.

34:04.330 --> 34:06.620
Who decides what makes sense?

34:08.040 --> 34:11.490
Nicky, you have no idea
what she's giving up.

34:11.690 --> 34:14.990
How much she's wanted this,
how much it means.

34:15.190 --> 34:17.370
Perhaps Petros is right.

34:17.570 --> 34:20.750
You don't need an audience
to make your music.

34:20.950 --> 34:22.750
Daisy isn't like Petros.

34:22.950 --> 34:24.750
She's not one of your friends

34:24.950 --> 34:26.960
writing sonnets
for fun on the weekends.

34:27.160 --> 34:29.100
She says she's happy.

34:31.150 --> 34:33.360
Do you not want her to be happy?

34:35.860 --> 34:37.720
Hey. What's going on here?

34:37.920 --> 34:39.870
[Nicky laughs softly]

34:41.120 --> 34:43.810
What do you say
we drop some acid...

34:44.010 --> 34:45.400
- Yes.
- ...and we swim out

34:45.600 --> 34:47.190
- to those rocks?
- I don't know if that's
a good idea right now.

34:47.390 --> 34:48.570
- I mean...
- Sounds great.

34:48.770 --> 34:51.590
Oh, good. Okay.

34:58.430 --> 35:00.680
[laughter]

35:04.100 --> 35:05.500
[water splashing]

35:05.700 --> 35:07.250
[whooping]

35:07.450 --> 35:08.750
<i>[Daisy] I don't think</i>

35:08.950 --> 35:10.170
Simone's having any fun.

35:10.370 --> 35:12.310
Of course she isn't.

35:13.440 --> 35:15.300
Why do you say that?

35:15.500 --> 35:17.300
Nothing. Just, um,

35:17.500 --> 35:19.310
I don't think
she approves of me is all.

35:19.500 --> 35:21.310
- I don't think that's it.
I think she's just...
- Ah.

35:21.510 --> 35:23.100
- ...doesn't know you very well.
- It's nothing personal.

35:23.300 --> 35:25.950
She just...
wants you all to herself.

35:27.000 --> 35:29.120
What are you talking about?

35:32.210 --> 35:34.210
Daisy.

35:36.960 --> 35:38.970
She's in love with you.

35:42.090 --> 35:43.950
That's crazy.

35:44.150 --> 35:45.460
You see it, don't you?

35:45.660 --> 35:47.120
I mean, the way
she looks at you,

35:47.320 --> 35:48.630
the way she follows you around.

35:48.830 --> 35:50.920
I mean, she-she flew
halfway around the world

35:51.120 --> 35:52.760
at the drop of a hat
because you asked her to.

35:52.950 --> 35:54.380
Yeah, and I would do
the same thing for her

35:54.580 --> 35:56.090
- if she had wrote me...
- It's not her fault.

35:56.290 --> 35:58.760
I'm not blaming her. I mean...

35:58.960 --> 36:01.450
I mean, who wouldn't be
in love with you?

36:09.160 --> 36:11.150
[door opens]

36:11.350 --> 36:13.530
[door closes]

36:13.730 --> 36:15.710
[cat mews]

36:24.850 --> 36:26.970
[Daisy] You're not
leaving yet, are you?

36:30.390 --> 36:32.550
Soon.

36:32.740 --> 36:35.130
Figure we could have breakfast,

36:35.330 --> 36:37.340
go for one last swim?

36:37.540 --> 36:40.010
I have a better idea.

36:40.210 --> 36:41.680
You stay for one more week.

36:41.880 --> 36:43.820
Hmm.

36:45.410 --> 36:48.100
I mean, we've barely had
any time together, Simone.

36:48.300 --> 36:51.080
You haven't been
to the other side of the island.

36:55.960 --> 36:58.590
One more week.
Bernie will love it.

36:59.920 --> 37:01.450
I really got to get back.

37:01.650 --> 37:03.950
You don't have to do anything.

37:04.150 --> 37:06.580
I do. [smacks lips]

37:06.780 --> 37:09.210
I have shows booked,

37:09.410 --> 37:11.330
and bills to pay,

37:11.530 --> 37:14.100
- responsibilities.
- [Nicky clears throat]

37:15.150 --> 37:17.980
I'll, um, make some tea.

37:22.070 --> 37:23.600
Well, you used to be fun.

37:23.800 --> 37:25.430
I don't know what happened.

37:25.630 --> 37:27.930
Well,

37:28.130 --> 37:30.850
some of us have to work, Daisy.

37:31.050 --> 37:33.770
Some of us have
to work our damn asses off

37:33.970 --> 37:36.610
to get even half the breaks
you've gotten.

37:36.810 --> 37:38.610
I don't know
what's going on with you.

37:38.810 --> 37:41.250
- With me?
- Yeah.

37:46.760 --> 37:49.050
You remember when we first met?

37:51.180 --> 37:53.750
[Simone chuckles]

37:53.950 --> 37:57.590
You were that shy little girl,

37:57.790 --> 38:01.800
walking around with your book,

38:02.000 --> 38:03.840
too scared to play your songs
for anyone.

38:04.040 --> 38:05.470
- Yes, I remember.
- And what did I say to you?

38:05.670 --> 38:08.810
You told me to get on stage,
Simone, and I did that.

38:09.010 --> 38:10.390
And I was miserable.

38:10.590 --> 38:12.810
And you think
you're gonna be happy here?

38:13.010 --> 38:15.310
Daisy, I know you.

38:15.510 --> 38:17.690
You don't write music
just to write.

38:17.890 --> 38:20.650
You need to be heard,
you need to connect.

38:20.850 --> 38:22.450
- I'm not going back.
- You have to.

38:22.650 --> 38:24.780
- I can't.
- You have a number one single.

38:24.980 --> 38:27.830
- You have an album
that's going there.
- I don't care.

38:28.030 --> 38:29.830
- I don't care about any of it!
- Oh, my God. Yes, you do.

